article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 74, Idaho 56
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Michael Hale III scored 26 points and UTSA won its third straight game, defeating Idaho 74-56 Thursday night. Kannon Burrage added 16 points and Jeromie Hill had 12 for the Roadrunners (8-19, 3-12 Western Athletic), who shot 54.5 percent from the field and committed just six turnovers. Mike McChristian led Idaho (10-17, 5-11) with 19 points. Kyle Barone added 13 points and 15 rebounds, and Connor Hill scored 10 points. UTSA trailed by two at halftime but took control with a 20-3 run to open the second half. Hale scored nine points during the spurt, which put the Roadrunners ahead 58-43 with 11:03 remaining. The Vandals, who shot 53 percent from the field before the break, hit just 24 percent in the second half while scoring 16 points. The Roadrunners' win avenged a 74-70 loss at Idaho on Jan. 26.
